window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Most people love in shades of grey. Tom loves in shades of black and white. Take a journey with this newly diagnosed Aspie (Asperger's Syndrome) to see if his way of loving another human being can match up to a woman's idea of love. </p> <p>After receiving a diagnosis of Asperger Syndrome, Tom sets out on a mission to learn social skills, so he can get a woman to be attracted to him. Tom works very hard at becoming the man he thinks women want and is surprised when women still do not find him attractive. Then he develops a dark mental illness that takes him out of the dating game and into a fight for his life. </p> <p>Coming out of fighting for his love, Tom develops a new appreciation for himself and feels worthy of love once again. This time he decides against learning social skills or trying to understand the different shades of grey most people experience and love with. Now Tom loves in shades of black and white, which is who he is. Will being true to himself and loving another person in shades of black and white be good enough for the woman of his dreams? </p> <p>Listen to book one in this awesome series to begin exploring love through the eyes of an Aspie.</p>"; 
